# We'll create a simple check_solution.py that tests the solution against samples and some additional tests
import subprocess, sys, sys
from textwrap import dedent

def run(input_s):
    p = subprocess.Popen([sys.executable, 'solution.py'], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(input_s, timeout=2)
    return p.returncode, out, err

tests = [
    ("3\n", "333\n"),
    ("9\n", "999999999\n"),
    ("1\n", "1\n"),
    ("5\n", "55555\n"),
]

all_ok = True
for inp, expected in tests:
    rc, out, err = run(inp)
    ok = (out == expected) and (rc == 0)
    print(f"Input: {inp.strip()} | Expected: {expected.strip()} | Got: {out.strip()} | OK: {ok}")
    if not ok:
        all_ok = False

print('ALL_OK:', all_ok)
